For an Angular project, the .dockerignore is quite similar to the Node.js one, but with a few specific additions related to the Angular CLI and browser testing tools.

Create a file named .dockerignore in your Angular project root and paste the following:

Plaintext
# Dependency directories
# We want to install these fresh inside the container
node_modules/

# Angular build output
# If you have a local 'dist' folder, don't copy it; 
# the Dockerfile will build a fresh one.
dist/
.angular/

# Logs
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
logs/
*.log

# IDEs and Editors
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
.project
.classpath
.factorypath

# Unit Testing and Coverage
coverage/
.karma/
chrome_debug.js

# OS Metadata
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Version Control
.git/
.gitignore

# Docker
Dockerfile
.dockerignore